---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const meta = {
  title: "Privacy Policy | NumbKit",
  description: "How NumbKit handles your data: cookies, analytics, advertising, your rights under GDPR, CCPA, LGPD, LFPDPPP and Argentine Law 25.326.",
  canonical: "https://numbkit.com/privacy/",
  lang: "en",
  slug: "privacy",
};
const schemaOrg = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Privacy Policy",
  "url": "https://numbkit.com/privacy/",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "NumbKit",
    "url": "https://numbkit.com"
  }
};
---
<BaseLayout meta={meta} schemaOrg={schemaOrg}>
  <article style="max-width:720px;margin:2rem auto;color:var(--color-muted);line-height:1.8;padding:0 1rem">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 27 April 2026</em></p>

    <h2>1. Data Controller / Responsable del Tratamiento</h2>
    <p>The controller of personal data processed through this website is <strong>Leticia Verónica Minujen</strong>, an individual (persona física) with Argentine tax identification CUIT 27-28281739-5, domiciled in the Autonomous City of Buenos Aires, Argentina, operating the brand "NumbKit". To exercise data-subject rights, request the full legal address, or submit any privacy-related enquiry, write to <strong>privacy@numbkit.com</strong>.</p>

    <h2>2. Scope</h2>
    <p>This policy applies to <a href="https://numbkit.com">numbkit.com</a> ("the site") and explains what data we collect, how we use it, and the rights granted to you under the laws applicable to your jurisdiction, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Argentina — Ley 25.326 de Protección de los Datos Personales</li>
      <li>European Union & United Kingdom — GDPR / UK-DPA 2018</li>
      <li>California — CCPA / CPRA 2026 amendments</li>
      <li>Mexico — Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los Particulares (LFPDPPP)</li>
      <li>Colombia — Ley 1581 de 2012</li>
      <li>Brazil — Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (LGPD)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. What We Collect</h2>
    <p>Our calculators run entirely in your browser. We do <strong>not</strong> require accounts, do not store your inputs on our servers, and do not maintain a user database.</p>
    <p>However, the following third-party services automatically collect limited data when you visit:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> (hosting & security): server logs including IP address, browser type, and pages visited. Used solely for security and abuse prevention. Logs are retained for up to 30 days.</li>
      <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> (advertising): cookies and identifiers used to serve relevant ads under the IAB Europe Transparency and Consent Framework v2.3. Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (when active): anonymized traffic statistics. IP addresses are anonymized before storage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Processing Agreements</h2>
    <p>We rely on Data Processing Agreements (DPAs) with our technology providers (Cloudflare, Google) included in their standard service terms. These agreements ensure that data processing is limited to the purposes described in this policy and that adequate safeguards are in place for international transfers, including Standard Contractual Clauses where applicable.</p>

    <h2>5. Cookies and Consent</h2>
    <p>We use a Consent Management Platform (CMP) compatible with the IAB TCF v2.3 framework to comply with GDPR (EU/UK), CCPA (California), and similar regulations. On your first visit you can choose:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong> — accept advertising and analytics cookies</li>
      <li><strong>Do not consent</strong> — basic functionality only, non-personalized ads</li>
      <li><strong>Manage</strong> — granular control per purpose</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can withdraw your consent at any time, with the same ease with which it was granted, via the consent link in the footer. Our CMP also honours the Global Privacy Control (GPC) signal where supported by your browser.</p>

    <h2>6. Google AdSense — Ad Technology Partners</h2>
    <p>We participate in Google AdSense's automated optimization of advertising technology partners (ATP). Google may experiment with different ad-tech vendors that comply with 2026 privacy standards. You can review and manage the full list of these partners at any time through our cookie preference centre.</p>

    <h2>7. Notice at Collection (California Residents — CCPA/CPRA 2026)</h2>
    <p>At the moment of your access to this site, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> IP address, advertising cookies, device identifiers</li>
      <li><strong>Internet activity:</strong> interactions with calculators and pages visited</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These categories are <strong>"shared"</strong> with Google AdSense for the purpose of cross-context behavioural advertising. Retention periods: security logs 30 days; cookie data per the preferences set in our CMP. You have the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of your personal information through the "Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information" link in our footer, or by activating Global Privacy Control in your browser.</p>

    <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data held about you</li>
      <li><strong>Rectification</strong> of incomplete or inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Erasure / Cancellation</strong> of your data, where no legal retention duty applies</li>
      <li><strong>Opposition</strong> to processing for advertising or profiling</li>
      <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> previously given</li>
      <li><strong>Portability</strong> (where applicable under GDPR or LGPD)</li>
      <li><strong>Lodge a complaint</strong> with your local data protection authority (AAIP in Argentina, ICO in the UK, CPPA in California, INAI in Mexico, SIC in Colombia, ANPD in Brazil)</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Mexico — LFPDPPP:</strong> Mexican users may exercise their ARCO rights (Acceso, Rectificación, Cancelación, Oposición) or revoke their consent for advertising purposes by writing to <strong>privacy@numbkit.com</strong>. Requests are answered within 20 business days as required by INAI.</p>

    <h2>9. Para Usuários no Brasil (LGPD)</h2>
    <p>Em conformidade com a Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (Lei 13.709/2018), garantimos aos titulares brasileiros os direitos de confirmação da existência de tratamento, acesso, correção, eliminação, portabilidade e oposição. O canal de comunicação para questões de privacidade é <strong>privacy@numbkit.com</strong>.</p>

    <h2>10. Affiliate Links</h2>
    <p>Some links on NumbKit are affiliate links — primarily to Binance. If you sign up through one of these links and complete certain actions, we may receive a commission at no extra cost to you. Affiliate links are marked with <code>rel="sponsored"</code> as required by Google's guidelines.</p>

    <h2>11. Digital Products (Gumroad as Merchant of Record)</h2>
    <p>If you purchase a digital product from NumbKit, the transaction is processed by <strong>Gumroad Inc.</strong>, who acts as the Merchant of Record. Gumroad is responsible for collecting and remitting any applicable VAT or sales tax in your jurisdiction, and serves as the data controller for purchase information. We do not handle, store, or access payment data. See <a href="https://gumroad.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gumroad's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>12. Children</h2>
    <p>NumbKit is not directed to children under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.</p>

    <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy as the site evolves or as regulations change. The "Last updated" date above reflects the most recent revision.</p>

    <h2>14. Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights: <strong>privacy@numbkit.com</strong></p>

    <h2>15. Related Documents</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/disclaimer/">Legal Disclaimer</a></li>
      <li><a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a></li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
